headline: 3 Reasons to Avoid NCLH and 1 Stock to Buy Instead
summary: Over the past six months, Norwegian Cruise Line’s stock price fell to $18.74. Shareholders have lost 5.1% of their capital, which is disappointing considering the S&P 500 has climbed by 13.4%. This was partly due to its softer quarterly results and may have investors wondering how to approach the situation.
